    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Calling out \"petty\" behavior is often too emotionally loaded, so pivot the energy into its observable result; frame it as consistently \"creating unnecessary process friction.\" You can state that their contributions sometimes lack a constructive objective and divert from shared goals. This technique allows you to address the undesirable *pattern* of behavior without assigning them the dramatic label of a \"troublemaker.\" You are managing workflow, not judging their inner state.",
      "source": "target",
